equipment, planned air monitoring strategies, and a detailed description of the method to be employed in order 
to control environmental pollution.  The plan must also include (both fire and medical emergency) response plans 
and an Activity Hazard Analyses (AHAs) in accordance with <RID>EM 385-1-1</RID>.  The Asbestos Hazard Abatement Plan must 
be approved in writing prior to starting any asbestos work.  The Contractor, Asbestos Hazard Control Supervisor,, 
CP and PQP must meet with the Contracting Officer prior to beginning work, to discuss in detail the Asbestos 
Hazard Abatement Plan, including work procedures and safety precautions.  Once approved by the Contracting Officer, 
